Of this insect 1 have seen three specimens of the typical form, including the type: one of these has the scutellum yellow and the elytral punctuation finer. 0. salebram is based upon a pallid example of the same species; and the var. β, of which four specimens have been obtained, is probably a small smooth form of it. 0. infantula closely resembles 0. luqubris, but may be known from it by the single (post-median) transverse black fascia on the elytral margins, We figure Boheman's types, both of which are contained in the Baly collection.
